aws::graph::propositions: # Kitfox Super Sport Aircraft Accident Information
The defining event was loss of control in flight during takeoff.
The aircraft dragged wing/rotor/float/other during takeoff.
The pilot held a Commercial certificate.
The pilot was a 69-year-old male.
The pilot had airplane ratings for single-engine land.
The pilot had airplane ratings for single-engine sea.
The pilot had airplane ratings for multi-engine land.
The pilot occupied the left seat.
The pilot had no other aircraft ratings.
The pilot had an instrument rating for airplane.
No second pilot was present during the accident.
The pilot had no instructor ratings.
No toxicology was performed on the pilot.
The pilot held a Sport pilot medical certification.
The pilot's last flight review or equivalent was on August 7, 2012.
The pilot had 3750 hours of total flight time across all aircraft.
The pilot had 16 hours of flight time in this make and model.
The aircraft make was ALBRIGHT STAN.
The aircraft registration was N960WM.
The aircraft model was KITFOX SUPER SPORT.
The aircraft category was Airplane.
The aircraft was amateur built.
The aircraft had an Experimental light sport (Special) airworthiness certificate.
The aircraft serial number was KA09088156.
The aircraft had tailwheel landing gear.
The aircraft had 2 seats.
The last inspection of the aircraft was an Annual inspection on June 1, 2012.
The certified maximum gross weight of the aircraft was 1320 lbs.
The aircraft had 1 reciprocating engine.
The airframe had 71 total hours at the time of the accident.
The engine manufacturer was ROTAX.
The aircraft was equipped with a C91A Emergency Locator Transmitter that was not activated.
The engine model was 912UL.
The registered owner of the aircraft was Charles W d'Autremont.
The engine was rated at 80 Horsepower.
The operator of the aircraft was Charles W d'Autremont.
No operating certificates were held by the operator.
